HEADWORD: Thiophenol
<hw>Thi`o*phe"nol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thio-</ets> + <ets>phenol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless mobile liquid, <chform>C6H5.SH</chform>, of an
offensive odor, and analogous to phenol; -- called also <altname>phenyl
sulphydrate</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thiophthene</ent>⟦br⟧
